Plot.
George Sluizer's 1992 English-language remake of his 1988 Dutch thriller 
The Vanishing follows the same plot-line as the original film, yet with 
one important difference. The film details a young man's (Kiefer Sutherland) 
search for his girlfriend (Sandra Bullock), who disappeared at a gas station 
after the couple had a fight. Where the original film didn't reveal what 
happened to the girlfriend until late into the movie, the 1992 version opens 
with her kidnapper (Jeff Bridges) plotting his abduction. Over the course 
of the film, Sutherland's search for Bullock is intercut with footage of 
Bridges that illustrates his mental illness and his repeated attempts to 
abduct women.
